Your assessment that postgres has no vendor support, but does have third party support is technically accurate. However, CommandPrompt, EnterpriseDB, and and other third party support providers also contribute to the core product. Since there is no postgres &quot;vendor&quot; that has clear ownership of the copyright, but companies that employ code contributors full time, you end up with something close to vendor support. &lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Alos, you can buy a non-free closed source forke from these vendors that they have complete control over, and are more likely to customize than Microsoft or Oracle.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
CommandPrompt community contributors: http://www.commandprompt.com/community/&lt;br /&gt;
EnterpriseDB community contributors: http://www.enterprisedb.com/resources-community/enterprisedb-community-contributions
